snippet: The police arrested several of the roughly 250 people who marched toward Zuccotti Park in the first of three days of events for the one-year anniversary of the movement.
abstract: New York City police arrest several of the roughly 250 people who march toward Zuccotti Park in the first of three days of events for the one-year anniversary of the Occupy Wall Street movement.
lead_paragraph: The police arrested several of the roughly 250 people who marched toward Zuccotti Park in the first of three days of events for the one-year anniversary of the movement.

headline.seo: As Occupy Wall St. Turns One, Arrests Made at March
headline.main: Several Arrests at Occupy Wall Street March
headline.print_headline: As ‘Occupy’ Turns 1, Some Who March Are Arrested
